gui.aoa3.adventGui.help.description:
Advent of Ascension is a massive mod, covering a lot of different areas of Minecraft; so don't be surprised if you find yourself a bit lost. Not to worry though, there is a few things that can be done.

If you're looking for some specific information on any part of the mod, you will almost certainly be able to find the information you're looking for on the official wiki. The link to the wiki can be found on the right. If this isn't quite what you're looking for, you may also be able to find help in the Guides tab, on the left. This tab contains little information bundles about various parts of the game that you may need help with.

If you still can't find what you're looking for, join us on the official Discord server and ask any questions you want, there's plenty of knowledgeable players to help you out!

message.dialogue.creeponiaBlankRealmston: I've heard legends of these things. Here, I'll give you this for it
Take this, I have a strange urge to give it to you..
Woah, as soon as you came to me this weird stone appeared in my pocket. Do you know what it is?
message.dialogue.gorb_citizen.0: Gorb: It's weird, this place isn't real but apparently some creatures have escaped.
message.dialogue.gorb_citizen.1: Gorb: If you see any blue walking fungi, don't eat it.
message.dialogue.gorb_citizen.2: Gorb: I'd never mine under this surface. It's weird enough up here!
message.dialogue.gorb_citizen.4: Gorb: I wouldn't advise going for a swim.
message.dialogue.primordial_guide.0: Primordial Guide: Beware the red eyes, they are not a good omen.
message.dialogue.primordial_guide.1: Primordial Guide: Legends tell of a group of Primordial warriors that once roamed the lands.
message.dialogue.primordial_guide.2: Primordial Guide: Be careful of the Stalker Prime! They will sneak up on you before you know it.
message.dialogue.primordial_guide.3: Primordial Guide: Stock up from the Primordial Merchants before you leave.
message.dialogue.primordial_guide.4: Primordial Guide: Merkyres live in towers that are located throughout Dustopia.
message.dialogue.primordial_guide.5: Primordial Guide: You will need a source of light with you if you intend to journey about.
message.dialogue.primordial_guide.6: Primordial Guide: There are very dangerous creatures around here. Luckily most are locked up.
message.dialogue.primordial_guide.7: Primordial Guide: The darkness is ever-present in this world.
message.dialogue.zal_child.1: Zal Child: I'm not supposed to talk to strangers.
message.dialogue.zal_child.2: Zal Child: Catch me if you can!
message.dialogue.zal_child.3: Zal Child: You have a big head.
message.dialogue.zal_citizen.0: Zal Citizen: I'd never mine into a lunar island. The reward isn't worth the risk!
message.dialogue.zal_citizen.1: Zal Citizen: I dropped my silver coin and can't seem to find it anywhere.
message.dialogue.zal_citizen.2: Zal Citizen: I'm really afraid of those prisons floating about.
message.dialogue.zal_citizen.4: Zal Citizen: How do you see anything from up there?
message.dialogue.zal_citizen.alienOrb: Zal Citizen: You shouldn't have brought that here! Get it away from me!
